    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow Parents Legal Access To Medical Records & DNA Of Their Deceased Child",
        "additional_details": "Disease related death is very common, leaving some parents with unanswered questions because they can't access their deceased childs medical records.\r\n\r\nOns.gov.uk have recorded that in the year ending March 2020, female victims were more commonly killed by a partner, ex-partner or a family member. BBC reported that 173 people were killed in domestic violence-related homicides.\r\n\r\nIn cases where the next of kin of the deceased is not the parent of the deceased and is denied access to Medical records.",
        "background": "I would like the government to allow parents the legal right to access their deceased child's medical records and test their child's DNA if they so require.",
